Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine light buff-brown. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 31, 28. Name Xenotimos
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0560)
